text: Vana (or with diacrits, e.g. Váňa) may refer to: * Vana, Gujarat, a village on Saraushtra peninsula, western India * Vana State, a former princely state whose seat was in Vana, Gujarat * Vana, Iran, a village in Mazandaran Province, Iran * Váňa, a Czech surname * Vána, a fictional character from J. R. R. Tolkien's legendarium
title: Vana
